Nine people died last week when the taxi they were travelling in overturned and slammed into a bus stop. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng community safety MEC Sizakele Nkosi-Malobane says she will assist the families of the nine victims, who died in a taxi accident on the R82 in Walkerville, with the funeral arrangements.They died last week when the taxi they were travelling in overturned and slammed into a bus stop.Nkosi-Malobane visited the families on Friday, accompanied by senior officials from law enforcement agencies.She says she is saddened by the tragedy, as most of the deceased were breadwinners.The MEC s spokesperson Ndivhuho Gadisi said, The MEC saw it fit that as part of her responsibilities, to visits some of the families affected by that accident, to offer her support and to assist where possible in terms of burials and other related matters. 